  "body": "Thanks to @liggitt   and @timothysc for helping me figure this out.  Turns out there is a bug that i ran into in testing #13152 .\n\nFor example.  If you try to connect using kubeconfig w/ a client-certificate = .... but your ignoring tls, the client will try to use the certs anyway.   This results in an `x509...` error, because the kubelet is wants to do  a TLS handshake.\n\nIn otherwords `--skip-tls-verify` is overriden if certs are provided, which is very counterintuitive.\n\nBest solution: Fail fast if a user accidentally provides BOTH certs AND `skip-tls-verify` : Clearly any user doing this has no idea how to properly launch the kubelet.  I speak from personal experience :)\n",
